<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+2>ESSENTIAL BACKGROUND</FONT></B></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></CENTER>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1></FONT></B>

<br>
<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>PERFORMANCE METRICS</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>concurrency</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>definition: the maximum number of clients that can independently
access a multimedia document</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>higher concurrency&nbsp; minimizes the need for document
replication</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>access latency</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>definition: amount of time a client has to wait after sending
a request to the server, to receive the multimedia document</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>operation latency</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>definition: amount of time required for an interactive operation
such as fast forward or pause to be effective</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>should be independent of the load of the server</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>scalability</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>the throughput should scale with the number of clients</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>the server should support heterogeneous clients and multimedia
data</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>extendibility</FONT></B></LI>

<UL><li><FONT SIZE=+1>the server should support all possible application
scenarios
and service models</il></FONT></UL>
</UL>

